utist.<ref>[https://www.usatoday.com/story/entertainment/music/2020/03/16/flutist-music-trailblazer-doriot-anthony-dwyer-dies-98/5064794002/ Doriot Anthony Dwyer, second ever female principal chair at major U.S. orchestra, dies at 98]</ref>\n*[[Ren\u00e9 Follet]], 88, Belgian illustrator, comics writer and artist.<ref>[https://www.actualitte.com/article/bd-manga-comics/deces-de-l-illustrateur-et-dessinateur-rene-follet/99731 D\u00e9c\u00e8s de l'illustrateur et dessinateur Ren\u00e9 Follet] {{in lang|fr}}</ref>\n*[[Jon Atle Gaarder]], 85, Norwegian diplomat, ambassador to Saudi Arabia (1984\u20131990), India (1990\u20131994) and Lithuania (1999\u20132001).<ref>[https://snl.no/Jon_Atle_Gaarder Jon Atle Gaarder] {{in lang|no}}</ref>\n*[[Giancarlo Ghironzi]], 88, Sammarinese politician, [[Captain Regent of San Marino|Captain Regent]] (1961, 1969\u20131970).<ref>[https://www.sanmarinortv.sm/news/attualita-c4/si-e-spento-giancarlo-ghironzi-a185102 Si \u00e8 spento Giancarlo Ghironzi] {{in lang|it}}</ref>\n*[[Mubashir Hassan]], 98, Pakistani politician, [[Finance, Revenue and Economic Affairs Minister of Pakistan|Minister of Finance]] (1971\u20131974).<ref>[https://www.thenews.com.pk/latest/629063-founding-ppp-member-mubashir-hasan-passes-away-in-lahore-family-source Founding PPP member Mubashir Hasan passes away in Lahore: family sources]</ref>\n*[[Galen Head]], 72, Canadian ice hockey player ([[Detroit Red Wings]]).<ref>[https://www.tribdem.com/news/local_news/mike-mastovich-johnstown-hockey-icon-galen-head-passes-away-at/article_e18e0986-66f8-11ea-bb68-87c7a0a95e5a.html Mike Mastovich | Johnstown hockey icon Galen Head passes away at 72]</ref>\n*[[Dave Mounfield]], 50, English actor and comedian (''[[Count Arthur Strong's Radio Show!]]''), cancer.<ref>[https://www.chortle.co.uk/news/2020/03/15/45638/count_arthur_strong_cast_member_dies Count Arthur Strong cast member dies]</ref>\n*[[Tamaki Nakanishi]], 44, Japanese voice actress (''[[Accel World]]'', ''[[Gad Guard]]'',